# Setup & Smoke Test

## Install
1. Arduino IDE → **Boards Manager** → Arduino **mbed_giga** (latest).
2. Libraries: **ArduinoJson**, **WiFi** (GIGA), **mcp2515**.
3. Place your sketch at `src/VehicleSimulator_GIGA.ino`.

## Flash & First Boot
- Upload → open Serial @115200.
- Expect: `[KV] Loaded persistent values.`  
- If STA fails, AP starts; Serial prints SSID/IP (often `192.168.3.1`).

## Smoke Test
1. Web UI: turn **Ignition On**.
2. Set speed (or Cruise ON + Set Speed).
3. Confirm **Engine Hours** and **Odometer** increase.
4. Toggle ignition OFF after ≥2 min → expect `[KV] Saved (end-of-drive).`
5. Reboot → values resume.

## Troubleshooting
- Hours not changing: ensure **Ignition On**.
- Odo not changing: ensure **Speed > 0** (or Cruise active).
- If UI posts keep resetting counters, disable odometer/engineHours writes from web POST or gate them behind a flag.
